    • deposit

      public boolean deposit(Account account, double amount)
      Deposit a specified amount into a specific account if the account exists and the amount is non-negative. If the account is a MoneyMarket account, it deposits the amount into the MoneyMarket account, otherwise, it adds the amount to the account's balance.
      Parameters:
      account -
      amount -
      Returns:
      true if the deposit was successful, false if the account doesn't exist, the amount is negative, or if the account is not a MoneyMarket account
